snippet.textDisplay: The Budapest question: Thinking Europe is a country, fine, that is base base general knowledge, but I really hate people who bash for not knowing where on a map a certain country is, or what city is capital of what...it is useless specific knowledge to your everyday life, unless your work requires you to know this, it is simply not something the average person even thinks of or has to think of, along with a bunch of other useless shit we learn in school. There is no shame in forgetting or not caring about information like that. Broad general knowledge is one thing, but the pedantic attitude towards not knowing less important stuff is getting tiresome nowadays
